Lutherans across 36 states and FCT, have converged for the 95th Annual Convention of the Lutheran Church of Christ in Nigeria (LCCN) in Adamawa state. The annual event organized in Demsa was declared by His Grace, Most Rev. Musa Panti Filibus where Christians were charged to sustain the unity of the spirit through bond of peace. Filibus also charged the faithfuls not allow opinion to over-raid love and tolerance by many forces causing fears and suspicions. He lamented increasing insecurity remains as major challenge bedeviling the country. “On daily bases our lives is marked by violence due to activities of religious insurgents, fully armed herdsmen, abduction for ransom, murders, rape, forceful conversion and many atrocities bedeviling the country. “We insist on mutual dialogue as the way of peace, justice and peaceful coexistence.” The cleric urged those conferred with constitutional responsibility for the protection of citizens to employ every means possible to put an end to undesirable activities. The General Secretary All Africa Conference of Churches Rev Dr Fidon Mwombeki of the Evangelical Lutheran Church of Tanzania, stated that a church in a country of conflict is a church in conflict. Mwombeki stressed the need Christians to be vanguard of peace through commitment to fervent prayers. 